name: Standar Lokal (Urutan Babi Asap)
address: Jalan Pura Luhur Batukaru, Wongaya Gede, Kec. Penebel, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: One of our favorite meals in Bali! Concept cooking by a very sophisticated chef. Village style omakese for 120k two persons. By reservation only. We tried authentic Indonesian food that we never tasted before. Simple but creative and delicious. Highly recommend if you stay at Tepi Sawah !
review 2:

You can DM them on Instagram to confirm a time slot before visiting! We‚Äôre the first foreigners to visit and I‚Äôm sure we won‚Äôt be the last. Thank you for the food and conversations ‚ò∫Ô∏è
review 3: Thank you Gede and your family for best sausage and smoked chicken. Bravo for vegetable and spices and all atmosphere in the jungle. For sure we gonna visit you again. By from Dominik and Martine.
review 4: highly recomended! best food, ambiance, cute dogs, everythings just too perfect for a short gateway from the city! definitely will be back
review 5: Although there was no food left for dinner, we've been offered a great tea and water and had the chance to spend a great time with Imran and Tukut! We would definitely come back to try out the food!

name: TEGAL JERO Homestay
address: Jalan Penatahan - Wongaya Gede, J485+G9H, Penebel, Wongaya Gede, Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82152, Indonesia
review 1:
My first trip to bali.i flew from Australia and my aunty from India. We were worried when we arrived late at night. But next day with day break we were overjoyed. Beautiful garden view for our bungalow.
Mountain River and rain forests on right side of bungalow.  We felt calm relaxed and enjoyed the peace
Eftpos sometimes don't work. I didn't understand currency. Adi was very humble to politely explain to us.
He and his wife  is amazing cook . I ordered papaya soup must try.

My heart felt review bali people are humble,honest, polite and very happy.
We are coming back with our family
review 2:
üåø‚ú® Tranquil Retreat in Nature: TEGAL JERO Homestay ‚ú®üè°

Nestled on the journey to the mountain, TEGAL JERO Homestay is a true haven surrounded by a lush forest. The combination of traditional houses and cabins adds to the charm, providing an authentic experience.

The property is a nature lover's dream, with a gentle river flowing through and numerous trees creating a serene atmosphere. The staff is exceptionally friendly, ensuring a warm welcome and a peaceful stay.

It's a quiet escape, perfect for those seeking respite. Situated near Jatiluwuh and Batukaru, the homestay benefits from cool weather, offering a refreshing break from the constant activity in crowded places around the island. The owner's thoughtful touch of creating a special menu for Nasi Bakar enthusiasts like me added a personalized touch to the experience.

Cleanliness and order prevail throughout, making TEGAL JERO Homestay not just a place to stay but a serene retreat where every detail is taken care of.

review 4: Adi is an amazing host with a simple but cute homestay. He gave us a traditional Balinese room with an amazing view of the garden. There is access to a small river and he offers great trekking!! Would definitely recommend
review 5: We can definitely recommend this place! We had a great time here and with Adi had a great host. The place is really nice to come down and relax, since it's very quiet. Also the garden is beautiful and adds well to the great atmosphere providing great forest views.
